Boeing Co &lt;BA.N> said its Boeing Vertolhelicopter unit proposed that U.K. Helicopter maker &lt;WestlandPlc> should build up to a third of all future Chinooks forBritain's airforce.    A Boeing statement made here said the work would involve upto 12,500 man-hours per machine, and solve some of Westland'sshort-term workload problems. It comes amid speculation thatBritain may pull out of the European EH-101 project, with thepossibility of up to 2,000 Westland job losses.    Westland was rescued last year by United Technologies Corp&lt;UTX.N> and Fiat Spa &lt;FIAT.MI>. Reuter&#3;